main event: On 24 August 1957, two objects were observed in Bel Air, MD; one was white and round, hovering slowly to the northeast, and another star-like object moved rapidly to the northwest.
interesting points: The first object was the size of a half dollar, A total of over 10 objects were reported, The objects changed course during the observation, Multiple similar UFO reports were received during this period, The investigation hinted that the objects could be the moon or known planets.
sighted object: one white round object and one small star-like object
witness description: Military source; no specific witness information provided
